    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-27T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-27T13:00:00-05:00" n="328"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/4082: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-27T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 27, 1943—noon.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 28—4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>748. Department’s 1185, July 24. With minimum 2 months’ notice 500 to 1,000
                    additional refugees could be accomplished [<hi rend="italic">accommodated?</hi>]
                    in Colonia Santa Rosa.</p>
                <p>For additional large groups it would be necessary to establish new centers and we
                    would require 5 to 6 months’ advance notification.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
